      "span_text": "A pilot experiment was performed aimed at comparing the anti-tumor effect of 32 P-ATP with non-radiolabeled ATP. 24 nu/nu mice, inoculated subcutaneously with 2x10 6 HT-29 cancer cells, were subdivided into the following groups and received: 1) 32 P-ATP-treated (n = 8): a single intra venous (i.v.) injection of 32 P-ATP (3.7 MBq) at day 9 after HT-29 cell inoculation; 2) ATP-treated (n = 8): i.p injection of 1 ml of 25 mM ATP (pH 6.2) in PBS solution for 10 days starting from day 9 after HT-29 cell injection; 3) PBS-treated (n = 4): daily i.p. injection of 1 ml of PBS for 10 days; 4) non-treated (n = 4). [CITATION_1]"
